  "prompt": "Which is the best Android app locker?",
  "response": "As of the latest information up to 2023, several Android app lockers are considered very good due to their features, ease of use, and reliability. Here are some of the top picks:\n\n1. **AppLock by DoMobile Lab**: This is one of the most popular app lockers on the Play Store. It offers features like fingerprint locking, photo vault, and browser locking. It's highly customizable and supports multiple locking mechanisms.\n\n2. **Norton App Lock**: Known for its strong security features, Norton App Lock provides reliable app locking as well as anti-theft features. It is user-friendly and integrates well with other Norton security products.\n\n3. **Smart AppLock (App Protect)**: This app locker offers various security features such as locking apps with a password, pattern, or fingerprint. It also includes features like preventing uninstallation of apps and hiding app icons.\n\n4. **LOCKit**: LOCKit protects your apps, photos, videos, and private data with advanced security methods. It provides intruder selfies, safe app management, and can even hide notifications.\n\n5. **Perfect AppLock**: This app protects your apps with PIN, pattern, or gesture, and even includes screen filters to prevent snooping. It comes with features like remote app locking and locking device rotation.\n\nChoosing the best app locker depends on your specific needs such as the type of security you want (pattern, PIN, fingerprint), additional features (like intruder selfies, hiding notifications), and interface preferences. Always consider checking recent reviews and updates as new security features or changes may impact their effectiveness.",
